- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with private computation and capacity of private information retrieval schemes. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper deals with privacy and collusion of servers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses computation of functions on data stored across multiple servers. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with encoded data stored on servers. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the rate of computation for certain setups.
